{"@context":"https://www.hestia.earth/schema/Cycle.jsonld","createdAt":"2023-12-12","updatedAt":"2025-03-25","@id":"jgavivhk3lhz","@type":"Cycle","description":"Cycle represents all inputs associated with the rearing of all chicks, pullets and layer hens in order to produce 1000kg of eggs in non-organic free range systems.","endDate":"2010","cycleDuration":504,"startDateDefinition":"start of animal life","functionalUnit":"relative","functionalUnitDetails":"1000kg of eggs produced","site":{"@id":"avd-f4a66zr7","@type":"Site"},"defaultSource":{"@id":"fwy8ntyofqew","@type":"Source"},"defaultMethodClassification":"modelled","defaultMethodClassificationDescription":"The structural model calculated all of the inputs required to produce the functional unit, allowing for breeding overheads (3 generations of breeding stock), mortalities, and productivity levels. The general structure of the model was based on multiple linear equations, which were solved simultane- ously with a code written in Visual Basic for applications specifically for this purpose. A mechanistic animal growth and production model was used in the current study for 3 purposes: 1) to calculate the total consumption of each feed ingredient during the whole production cycle; 2) to calculate the amounts of main nutrients, N, P, and K, in manure pro- duced by the birds during the production cycle; and 3) to include the correlation between changes in the pro- duction figures (egg production, feed intake, and nutri- ent output) to be applied in the uncertainty analysis (see below). The model was based on the principles pre- sented by Emmans and Kyriazakis (2001) and Wellock et al. (2003), and predicted the daily feed intake, which varies considerably during the bird life cycle, of a single bird as a function of feed composition and energy and protein requirements of the bird. This included require- ments for both production (body growth and eggs) and maintenance.","treatment":"FreeRange","commercialPracticeTreatment":true,"numberOfReplications":1,"inputs":[{"term":{"@type":"Term","name":"Feed mix","termType":"processedFood","@id":"feedMix","units":"kg"},"value":[242.66666666666666],"impactAssessment":{"@id":"hjdhjw_2mmhi","@type":"ImpactAssessment"},"impactAssessmentIsProxy":false,"isAnimalFeed":true,"@type":"Input"},{"term":{"@type":"Term","name":"Feed mix","termType":"processedFood","@id":"feedMix","units":"kg"},"value":[364],"impactAssessment":{"@id":"ez-m3ojoxipx","@type":"ImpactAssessment"},"impactAssessmentIsProxy":false,"isAnimalFeed":true,"@type":"Input"},{"term":{"@type":"Term","name":"Feed mix","termType":"processedFood","@id":"feedMix","units":"kg"},"value":[202.22222222222223],"impactAssessment":{"@id":"u4xhbuamgf6r","@type":"ImpactAssessment"},"impactAssessmentIsProxy":false,"isAnimalFeed":true,"@type":"Input"},{"term":{"@type":"Term","name":"Feed mix","termType":"processedFood","@id":"feedMix","units":"kg"},"value":[1496.4444444444443],"impactAssessment":{"@id":"siygsajlzy0t","@type":"ImpactAssessment"},"impactAssessmentIsProxy":false,"isAnimalFeed":true,"@type":"Input"},{"term":{"@type":"Term","termType":"water","name":"Water, source unspecified","units":"m3","@id":"waterSourceUnspecified"},"value":[5.35],"operation":{"@type":"Term","name":"Providing animals with water","termType":"operation","@id":"providingAnimalsWithWater","units":"hour"},"@type":"Input"},{"term":{"@type":"Term","name":"Electricity, grid, market mix","termType":"electricity","@id":"electricityGridMarketMix","units":"kWh"},"value":[991.746],"description":"Used mainly for ventilation, automatic feeding and lighting","@type":"Input"},{"term":{"@type":"Term","termType":"fuel","name":"Fuel oil","units":"kg","@id":"fuelOil"},"value":[29.513888888888886],"methodClassification":"estimated with assumptions","methodClassificationDescription":"Gas and oil were aggregated together in the study. Have assumed an equal split between the two.","@type":"Input"},{"term":{"@type":"Term","termType":"fuel","name":"Propane","units":"m3","@id":"propane"},"value":[49.82415005861664],"methodClassification":"estimated with assumptions","methodClassificationDescription":"Gas and oil were aggregated together in the study. Have assumed an equal split between the two. Assuming \"gas\" is liquid propane based on Table 2.","@type":"Input"},{"term":{"@type":"Term","termType":"liveAnimal","name":"Layer chicken, chick","units":"number","@id":"layerChickenChick"},"value":[57.84946236559139],"properties":[{"term":{"@type":"Term","name":"Age","termType":"property","@id":"age","units":"days"},"value":1,"share":100,"@type":"Property"},{"term":{"@type":"Term","name":"Mortality rate","termType":"property","@id":"mortalityRate","units":"%"},"value":7,"share":100,"@type":"Property"}],"methodClassification":"estimated with assumptions","methodClassificationDescription":"Calculated using no. of layers / the mortality rate","isAnimalFeed":false,"@type":"Input"},{"term":{"@type":"Term","name":"Feed mix","termType":"processedFood","@id":"feedMix","units":"kg"},"value":[606.6666666666667],"impactAssessment":{"@id":"neivo8ogdlxh","@type":"ImpactAssessment"},"impactAssessmentIsProxy":false,"isAnimalFeed":true,"@type":"Input"},{"term":{"@type":"Term","name":"Wood (material)","termType":"material","@id":"woodMaterial","units":"kg"},"value":[16.4007243130227],"description":"Wood shavings for bedding","isAnimalFeed":false,"@type":"Input"}],"practices":[{"term":{"@type":"Term","name":"Stocking density, animal housing (average)","termType":"animalManagement","@id":"stockingDensityAnimalHousingAverage","units":"animals / m2"},"value":[6],"@type":"Practice"},{"term":{"@type":"Term","name":"Stocking density, temporary pasture (average)","termType":"animalManagement","@id":"stockingDensityTemporaryPastureAverage","units":"animals / m2"},"value":[0.1],"@type":"Practice"},{"term":{"@type":"Term","name":"Free range system","termType":"system","@id":"freeRangeSystem","units":"% area"},"value":[100],"@type":"Practice"},{"term":{"@type":"Term","name":"Hy-Line Brown","termType":"animalBreed","@id":"hyLineBrown","units":"%"},"value":[100],"@type":"Practice"}],"animals":[{"term":{"@type":"Term","termType":"liveAnimal","name":"Layer chicken, hen","units":"number","@id":"layerChickenHen"},"animalId":"Hens","value":43.419235364396656,"referencePeriod":"average","methodClassification":"estimated with assumptions","methodClassificationDescription":"Assuming laying phase lasts 56 weeks.","@type":"Animal"},{"term":{"@type":"Term","termType":"liveAnimal","name":"Layer chicken, chick","units":"number","@id":"layerChickenChick"},"animalId":"Chicks","value":4.6520609318996415,"referencePeriod":"average","methodClassification":"estimated with assumptions","methodClassificationDescription":"Assuming chicks are chicks for the first 6 weeks of life.","@type":"Animal"},{"term":{"@type":"Term","termType":"liveAnimal","name":"Layer chicken, pullet","units":"number","@id":"layerChickenPullet"},"animalId":"Pullets","value":7.753434886499402,"referencePeriod":"average","methodClassification":"estimated with assumptions","methodClassificationDescription":"Assuming pullet phase goes from 6 to 16 weeks.","@type":"Animal"}],"products":[{"term":{"@type":"Term","termType":"animalProduct","name":"Eggs, hen, in shell","units":"kg","@id":"eggsHenInShell"},"value":[1000],"primary":true,"properties":[{"term":{"@type":"Term","name":"Weight per item","termType":"property","@id":"weightPerItem","units":"kg"},"value":0.0635,"share":100,"@type":"Property"}],"@type":"Product"},{"term":{"@type":"Term","termType":"liveAnimal","name":"Layer chicken, hen","units":"number","@id":"layerChickenHen"},"value":[53.8],"methodClassification":"estimated with assumptions","methodClassificationDescription":"Assuming all hens are slaughtered at the end of the cycle.","properties":[{"term":{"@type":"Term","name":"Liveweight per head","termType":"property","@id":"liveweightPerHead","units":"kg liveweight / head"},"value":1.97,"share":1